{"lemma":"خَمِيس","slug":"خَمِيس","root":"خ.م.س","root_slug":"خ-م-س","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-م-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11506"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B3"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Thursday"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/xa.miːs/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11506","headword_ar":"خَمِيسٌ","root":"xms","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xumusN","text_ar":"خُمُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxomuwsN","text_ar":"مَخْمُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An army;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because consisting of five parts, namely, the van, the body, the right wing, the left wing, and the rear; (S, A, K;) or because the spoils are divided into fifths among it; but this latter assertion requires consideration; (ISd, MF;) for this division of the spoils is an affair of the Muslim law, whereas"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xmys","text_ar":"خميس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thus applied] is an old term: (MF:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an army having numerous weapons;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jayo$N xa$inN","text_ar":"جَيْشٌ خَشِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Alxamiysi","text_ar":"يَوْمُ الخَمِيسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and simply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxamiysu","text_ar":"الخَمِيسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thursday; the fifth day of the week;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaAmisu","text_ar":"الخَامِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in like manner as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~abaraAnu","text_ar":"الدَّبَرَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to the star [that follows the Pleiades, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAbiru","text_ar":"الدَّابِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axomisapN","text_ar":"اَخْمِسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axomisaA='u","text_ar":"اَخْمِسَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axaAmisu","text_ar":"اَخَامِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, TA.) AZ used to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaY","text_ar":"مَضَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxamiysu bimaA fiyhi","text_ar":"الخَمِيسُ بِمَا فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thursday passed with what"},{"kind":"text","text":"happened"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in it"},{"kind":"text","text":"], making it sing. and masc.: but Abu-l-Jarráh used to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaYAlxamiysu bima fiyhin~a","text_ar":"مَضَىالخَمِيسُ بِمَ فِيهِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", making it pl. and fem., and using it as a n. of number. (Lh, TA.) It has no dim. (Sb, S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ams","text_ar":"امس"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximosN","text_ar":"خِمْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last signification.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^adoriY A^aY~u xamiysi Aln~aAsi huwa","text_ar":"مَا اَدْرِى اَىُّ خَمِيسِ النَّاسِ هُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I know not what company of men it is."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-' Abbád, Sgh, K.)"}],"source_refs":["MF","S","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}